    "discriminators": [
     "A mass of snow collapsing is a WHUMP, not a crash: snow is a porous absorber, so the event is low (centroid ~900 Hz), steeply rolled off (-11 dB/oct), and essentially ringless (decay ~80 ms).",
     "Against ICE-CRASH & DEBRIS: the material-impedance axis at its widest. Ice debris clatters brightly (centroid ~3.2 kHz, bright shards, high transient count); snow debris has almost no high-frequency content and no resolvable shards. An octave and a half of centroid separates them — one of the more reliable material calls in this set.",
     "Against SNOW-IMPACT: a matter of scale and debris. UCS points the extreme version at NATURAL DISASTER-AVALANCHE; a discrete thud with no aftermath is SNOW-IMPACT.",
     "Softer attack than any hard-material crash: snow compresses before it fails."
