    "discriminators": [
     "A snowball hit or a body landing in a drift: a DULL, DARK, DEAD thud. Snow's porosity absorbs the high frequencies at the moment of impact, giving the lowest spectral_centroid_hz (~800 Hz) and the steepest spectral_slope_db_per_octave of any impact in this file set, with essentially no ring (decay ~50 ms).",
     "Against ICE-IMPACT: the cleanest material-impedance contrast available here. Ice clinks bright and brittle at ~3.6 kHz; snow thuds dark at ~0.8 kHz — over two octaves apart, plus a much softer attack (snow compresses, ice does not). This one really is separable on spectrum alone.",
     "Against SNOW-CRASH & DEBRIS: a crash is bigger, longer and leaves a debris tail; an impact is one discrete event.",
     "Against SNOW-HANDLE: HANDLE is a sustained crunch texture with no dominant transient."
